<HEADLINE>
UNDATED: for Pittsburgh.
</HEADLINE>
 &UR; Avalanche 4, Mighty Ducks 2 &QL; 

<TEXT>
	   At Anaheim, California, Milan Hejduk scored the go-ahead goal
for Colorado and goaltender Craig Billington got the win despite
playing less than two minutes and not facing a shot.
	   Billington replaced Patrick Roy in the nets for a span of 1:52
late in the second period, and was on the ice when Hejduk scored on
a power play with Kevin Haller serving a tripping penalty.
	   Roy returned with 20 seconds left in the period. He stopped 27
shots while playing 58:08 of the game, but didn't get a decision.
	   Claude Lemieux added an insurance goal with 7:53 left in the
game as the Avalanche won for the first time in five games and
ended the Mighty Ducks' six-game unbeaten streak.
</TEXT>
