<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-Iran-Missile </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Two stray missiles from attack on Iraq landed in Iran, paper says
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   TEHRAN, Iran (AP) _ Two stray missiles from the U.S.-British
attack on Iraq earlier this week fell on the city of Khorramshahr
in southern Iran, the Tehran Times reported Tuesday.
	   The official Islamic Republic News Agency had previously
reported that only one missile had hit Khorramshahr, about 40
kilometers (25 kilometers) east of Basra in Iraq. The first missile
struck the port city with major oil facilities on Thursday.
	   The paper did not say when the second missile was supposed to
have struck the city.
	   The first missile landed in the city center and damaged several
houses but did not cause any casualties, the paper said.
	   The second missile landed on a highway leading out of the city
and left a two-meter-long (six foot) hole, said the paper.
	   The United States apologized for the incident, said the paper,
which is close to the Foreign Ministry.
 &UR; fsa-ggl
</TEXT>
