<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-China-Death Sentence </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Beijing man sentenced to death for meteor shower rape, murder
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   BEIJING (AP) _ A Beijing court has given a death sentence to a
man convicted of raping and murdering a 14-year-old girl who had
stayed out during the pre-dawn hours of Nov. 18 to watch the
Leonids meteor storm, official reports said Tuesday.
	   Pang Delu, a road worker who had served a previous prison
sentence for theft, was found guilty of tricking the girl into
following him into a deserted area and raping her. When she
resisted, he strangled her to death, the Beijing Morning Post and
other local newspapers reported.
	   The Beijing No. 2 Intermediate Court handed down the sentence on
Monday, citing public anger over the crime. Pang also was ordered
to pay the girl's parents 30,000 yuan (dlrs 3,632) in compensation,
the reports said.	   
</TEXT>
