r s &Cx13;  &Cx11;  BC-Sports-Cricket-Englan     12-22 0142
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-Sports-Cricket-England-Australian XI </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Blewett makes short work of English bowlers
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   HOBART, Australia (AP) _ Greg Blewett and Corey Richards smashed
the Australian XI to a nine-wicket victory over England at
Bellerive Oval on Tuesday.
	   Blewett hit 213 and Richards 138 as the Australians made light
of a 376-run target from 78 overs.
	   The pair, who shared an unbroken 345-run stand, reached their
target in the 56th over.
	   England set the target when it declared its second innings on
Tuesday morning at 199-3 just after Mark Butcher completed his
century.
	   In the course of his innings Blewett joined two elite groups of
Australian cricketers.
	   He became only the sixth to pass 1,000 runs before the New Year,
then he became the sixth to score centuries in four successive
first-class innings. (djp) 	   
</TEXT>
