</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-India-Fog Accident,0119 </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Police: Fog causes truck to ram house, four killed
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   NEW DELHI, India (AP) _ Dense fog caused a truck to run into a
house near the Indian capital of New Delhi, killing two children
and injuring a third child and an adult as they slept, a newspaper
reported Tuesday.
	   Police believe the truck driver, who fled after Monday's
accident in the New Delhi suburb of Faridabad, probably could not
see where he was going, according to The Indian Express.
	   The fog, common across northern India in December, has been
particularly heavy this year, disrupting flight schedules and
slowing rail and road traffic. Conditions have been most dangerous
at night and in the early mornings. 	   
</TEXT>
