<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-Iran-Missile,0161 </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Two stray missiles from attack on Iraq landed in Iran, paper says
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   TEHRAN, Iran (AP) _ Two stray missiles from the recent
U.S.-British attack on Iraq fell on the city of Khorramshahr in
southern Iran, the Tehran Times reported Tuesday.
	   The official Islamic Republic News Agency previously reported
that one missile hit Khorramshahr, about 40 kilometers (25
kilometers) east of Basra in Iraq. The first missile struck the
port city with major oil facilities on Thursday.
	   The newspaper did not say when the second missile was supposed
to have struck the city.
	   The first missile landed in the city center and damaged several
houses but did not cause any casualties, the newspaper said.
	   The second missile landed on a highway leading out of the city
and left a 2-meter-long (6- foot) hole, said the paper.
	   The United States apologized for the incident, said the
newspaper, which is close to the Foreign Ministry. 	   
</TEXT>
