<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-India-Pornographic Ashram,0356 </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Police: Holy retreat turned into pornography production house
</HEADLINE>
 &UR; By JAIDEEP MAZUMDAR &QC; 
 &UR; Associated Press Writer &QC; 

<TEXT>
	   LUCKNOW, India (AP) _ Twelve people have been arrested for
turning what began as a spiritual retreat in one of northern
India's holiest cities into a pornography production house, police
said Tuesday.
	   Residents of Mathura staged a protest as the 12 were brought to
court Tuesday, two days after their arrest. The suspects, accused
of duping and blackmailing women into acting in pornographic films
as well as distributing the materials, were ordered held pending
completion of the police investigation. They face up to 10 years
imprisonment.
	   The faithful believe the Hindu god Krishna was born in Mathura,
140 kilometers (87 miles) southeast of New Delhi.
	   Police say disciples of a holy man known as Baba Krishna Das
have been producing pornographic photographs and videos for the
past two years in what was originally an ashram, or spiritual
retreat, established in Mathura three years ago. Das escaped arrest
but was being pursued.
	   ``The ashram inmates have confessed to filming scores of such
blue films and supplying hundreds of photographs to buyers,'' said
Deputy Superintendent of Police R.K. Shastri. ``They have also
admitted that Baba Krishna Das was the mastermind behind the whole
racket.''
	   Shastri said women would be lured to the ashram, where they
would be drugged, stripped and photographed. The nude photos would
be used to blackmail the women into posing for more photos or
performing sexual acts with ashram members before video camers.
	   After a series of raids on video cassette libraries in recent
months, police traced pornographic materials to Mathura. A police
officer posing as a pornographic movie distributor approached Das'
head disciple, known only as Devdas, and struck a deal.
	   Devdas was arrested Sunday when he handed over two cassettes and
several photographs. Eleven others were arrested in a subsequent
raid.
	   ``Since Baba Krishna Das was away on his morning walk at that
time, we could not arrest him,'' Shastri said. 	   
</TEXT>
(PROFILE
(WS SL:BC-India-Pornographic Ashram; CT:i; 
