<SLUG> BC-Hong Kong-Stocks </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Hong Kong share prices close generally lower
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   HONG KONG (AP) _ Share prices in Hong Kong closed generally
lower Tuesday as investors took profits following three consecutive
sessions of gains.
	   The blue-chip Hang Seng Index fell 73.45 points, or 0.7 percent,
closing at 10,322.56. On Monday, the index had gained 169.78
points.
	   Turnover fell to 2.452 billion Hong Kong dollars (U.S. dlrs 314
million), down from Monday's 4.171 billion Hong Kong dollars (U.S.
dlrs 534 million).
	   Brokers said share prices fell as investors took profits after
recent sharp gains.
	   They said investors were also concerned over the sharp decline
on the Japanese stock exchange, where the key Nikkei index fell 2.6
percent after the Finance Ministry's trust fund bureau said it
would stop buying government bonds in 1999.
	   The report raised fears that interest rates would rise in Japan,
driving up corporate borrowing costs.
	   Among losers, China Telecom fell 70 Hong Kong cents to 14.15,
Cathay Pacific fell 20 cents to 7.85, Bank of East Asia fell 15
cents to 13.85, and Swire Pacific ``A'' fell 10 cents to 35.90.
	   Remaining unchanged were HSBC Holdings at 198.50, and Sun Hung
Kai Properties at 57.25.
	   Going against the trend was Hang Seng Bank, which rose 75 cents
to 72.75. 	   
