<SLUG> BC-Russia-Yeltsin </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Yeltsin berates interior minister
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   MOSCOW (AP) _ President Boris Yeltsin gave a tongue lashing to
Russia's top policeman Tuesday, saying he had failed to stop the
falsification of crime statistics, a new report said.
	   Some police figures indicate that Russia's high crime rate has
gone down a bit in the last few years, but Yeltsin said his data
showed the opposite.
	   ``And you tell me everything is fine,'' Yeltsin told Interior
Minister Sergei Stepashin at the Kremlin meeting, according to the
Interfax news agency.
	   ``I treat you with trust and respect,'' Yeltsin said. ``I judge
your work by its results. But God forbid that you should
overestimate yourself a little bit or relax.''
	   Stepashin, who is responsible for the police force, has
acknowledged that police falsified crime figures to earn perks and
make themselves look good. But he promised Yeltsin that statistics
would no longer get any ``window-dressing.''
	   Yeltsin has been sidelined by a string of illnesses, but said
stopping crime remained one of his top priorities.
	   Yeltsin was recently hospitalized for two weeks to recover from
pneumonia. He was released about two weeks ago, and has been
holding regular meetings since then.
	   (nw/gm) 	   
</TEXT>
