<HEADLINE>
Uzbekistan coach dies of heart attack after Asian Games
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   BANGKOK, Thailand (AP) _ A coach from Uzbekistan's Asian Games
team has died of a heart attack in his hotel room, police said
Tuesday.
	   Evgeny Godlevsky, 63, was pronounced dead Monday on arrival at a
Bangkok hospital. He had complained earlier of chest pains at the
medical center of the athletes' village.
	   Godlevsky was the second Asian Games coach to die during his
trip to Bangkok for the regional Olympic-style event, which ended
Sunday.
	   Rizvi Fuulile Zain, swimming manager for the Sri Lankan team,
died of a heart attack Dec. 14. 	   
