<HEADLINE>
Havel leaves for three-week vacation in Canary Islands
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   PRAGUE, Czech Republic (AP) _ President Vaclav Havel and his
wife Dagmar left for a three-week vacation in Canary Islands, the
news agency CTK reported Tuesday.
	   The often-ill president recently recovered from a mild case of
flu and doctors recommended that he take a holiday for his health,
preferably on sea.
	   Havel chose Lanzarotte, one of the Canary Islands. Like last
year, King Juan Carlos invited him to stay at one of his
residences.
	   CTK said that Havel is accompanied by his personal doctor Ilja
Kotik and Dagmar's mother, Marketa Veskrnova.
	   Havel, 62, fought off a life-threatening case of pneumonia in
August and underwent emergency surgery for a ruptured colon in
April.
	   A former chain smoker, Havel has been hospitalized five times
since December 1996, when a third of his lung and a cancerous tumor
were removed.
	   (nr/js)
