<HEADLINE>
Report: Russia to design launch pad, sell booster rockets to
</HEADLINE>
Australia &QL; 

<TEXT>
	   MOSCOW (AP) _ Russia will provide Australia with booster rockets
and a newly designed launch pad for putting commercial satellites
into orbit, a news report said Tuesday.
	   Russia's Makeyev rocket company, from the Ural Mountains region
of Chelyabinsk, signed the deal with Australia's United Launch
Systems International last week, the Interfax news agency reported.
	   The Makeyev company is to design a launch pad in eastern
Australia and supply dozens of boosters over five years to the
Australian company, Interfax said.
	   The report did not specify the value of the contract, or when
the work was expected to begin.
