<HEADLINE>
British tourist dies in Singapore after struck by car
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   SINGAPORE (AP) _ A British tourist died in Singapore after he
was struck by a car just an hour after his arrival, state-run
television reported Tuesday.
	   John Alan, 63, was hit by a taxi Sunday morning as he was
crossing a road to buy breakfast less than an hour after he and his
wife arrived in the city-state by bus from Thailand.
	   He suffered a fractured skull, and died at Singapore General
Hospital on Monday night, the television news program said.
	   Alan's home town was not disclosed, and police and British High
Commission officials were unavailable for comment.
	   The accident happened one month after Neil Knotts, a 36-year old
Briton lecturing in Singapore, was killed in an unsolved
hit-and-run collision. 	   
