<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-Pope-Prayers </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Heading toward Jubilee year, John Paul II asks for prayers of
</HEADLINE>
faithful &QL; 
 &UR; AP Photos &QL; 

<TEXT>
	   VATICAN CITY (AP) _ Newly recovered from the flu, Pope John Paul
II on Tuesday asked the faithful to pray for him so he could keep
carrying out his duties as he starts the third decade of his
papacy.
	   John Paul spoke to Rome's cardinals in his annual state of the
church address. Although it focused mainly on the work of this past
year, the speech came in the run-up to the 2000 Jubilee Year that
will be a culminating event of his papacy.
	   ``I ask all to continue to pray so I can serve the Lord each day
with renewed love,'' John Paul said.
	   It was one of his first appearances after a flu last week that
sent his temperature to 38 Celsius (100 F), forcing him to cancel
some appointments.
	   The 78-year-old pontiff made it through the long address without
any obvious signs of discomfort _ no faltering, no coughing fits.
He lingered afterward to speak a few words with many of the
cardinals.
	   (ek/vls)
</TEXT>
