r s &Cx13;  &Cx11;  BC-Sports-Soccer-ParisSa     12-22 0182
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-Sports-Soccer-Paris Saint-Germain </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
New PSG president seeks to halt ``spiral to mediocrity''
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   PARIS (AP) _ Struggling French soccer giant Paris Saint-Germain
named Laurent Perpere as its new president on Tuesday.
	   Perpere replaces Charles Bietry, who quit the post Monday after
only five months in charge.
	   Perpere, 47, was previously director of finance at Canal Plus,
the pay television broadcaster that owns the club, the richest in
France.
	   Under Bietry, accused by some former players and officials of
interfering in team matters, PSG had a disastrous run of results
and was hampered by in-fighting.
	   It currently lies in 11th place in the French first division,
only seven points clear of the relegation zone.
	   Perpere said his aim was to qualify for European competition
next season.
	   ``The situation has not been easy for the players. We have seen
too many statements and counter-statements,'' Perpere told
reporters. ``The team is in a spiral of mediocrity and lacks
confidence. We need serenity and cohesion.''
	   (ae-dgs) 	   
</TEXT>
