<SLUG> BC-Bulgaria-Arms Smuggling </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Bulgaria thwarts illegal arm export
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   SOFIA, Bulgaria (AP) _ Bulgaria's security services have blocked
an attempt to export locally-manufactured, protable rockets to an
undisclosed African country which is under an international arms
embargo, an official said Tuesday.
	   Kiril Radev, head of Bulgaria's anti-organized crime service,
refused to provide any further details because the operation is
still underway.
	   Radev said agents seized the shipment this fall in cooperation
with ``specialized services'' of the United States and Britain.
	   ``This is an extremely serious case,'' Radev said. ``The plane
which was to be loaded with those weapons had landed in Bulgaria.''
	   Portable antitank and antiaircraft rockets are some of the
products in which Bulgaria's arms industry has specialized since
the Soviet era.
	   (vz/reid)
