entirely pleased with the 1999 budget, but his party will probably
support quick passage because of the country's financial turmoil.
RUSSIA-ECONOMY.
	   MADRID _ Christmas festivities got off to a jubilant start for
dozens of retirees in the southeastern town of La Union who had
shares in the total top prize of 42 billion (dlrs 300 million) in
Spain's Christmas lottery, _ billed as the world's richest.
SPAIN-CHRISTMAS LOTTERY.
	   SARAJEVO, Bosnia-Herzegovina _ After carving up Bosnia's
territory, the rival ethnic groups are now fighting over one of the
country's cultural treasures _ a 600-year-old Jewish holy book.
