	   FRANKFURT _ Amid jitters about a blackmail attempt against the
German railways, police arrested a man Tuesday for threatening to
blow up a train station. GERMANY-RAILWAY THREATS.
	   PARIS _ An Ariane rocket placed an U.S. telecommunications
satellite into orbit overnight, completing the European Space
Agency's 1998 commercial launch program, the agency said Tuesday.
FRANCE-ARIANE LAUNCH.
	   WARSAW _ A few hours before talks between his government and
union leaders, Prime Minister Jerzy Buzek said Tuesday he believes
a labor dispute that has sparked protests at more than 50 coal
mines can be resolved before Christmas. POLAND-MINERS.
	   LONDON _ Trade Secretary Peter Mandelson said Tuesday that he
had done nothing wrong in accepting a large loan from colleague who
is now under investigation by Mandelson's department.
BRITAIN-MANDELSON.
