<SLUG> BC-Britain-Diana's Butler </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Diana's butler loses charity job
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   LONDON (AP) _ Princess Diana's former butler has lost his job at
the charity set up in her memory.
	   Paul Burrell, 40, the man whom the late princess called ``my
rock,'' cleared out his desk Tuesday and said his goodbyes.
	   Burrell had been the chief fundraiser of the Diana, Princess of
Wales Memorial Fund, but was told that since the charity no longer
was actively raising money, the position wasn't necessary.
	   The fund's chief executive, Andrew Purkis, said he had offered
Burrell a new job as a roving ambassador for the charity, but that
he had refused.
	   Burrell spent the morning packing up boxes from his office, then
left the building saying only, ``I am very sad.''
	   Looking tearful, he hugged another fund employee, Jacqueline
Allen.
	   ``I think the general public know how much Paul has given to the
fund,'' she said later. ``I just think it is tragic that he is no
longer with it.''
	   The charity, which provides money for causes sponsored by the
late princess, will concentrate on managing its existing funds.
	   (acw-kg)
</TEXT>
