<HEADLINE>
Fire hits department store amid Christmas rush
</HEADLINE>
 &UR; AP Photos staffing &QL; 

<TEXT>
	   STOCKHOLM, Sweden (AP) _ Fire broke out after someone poured
gasoline on the lower floor of one of Stockholm's main department
stores as it was crowded with Christmas shoppers Tuesday, injuring
at least two people.
	   Police said they arrested one person in connection with the
fire, but details were not immediately available, the Swedish news
agency TT reported.
	   The store faces the Hoetorget square, directly across from the
city's main concert hall. Firemen clolsed off the square, which
includes about 20 covered stalls for vendors of produce and leather
and woolen goods.
	   One of those injured was taken to hospital for treatment of
smoke inhalation. The extent of the others' injuries were not
immediately known.
	   The fire caused little visible damage to the store and was
declared extinguished about 45 minutes after the alarm
	   (jh)
