<HEADLINE>
Five people die in cargo plane crash
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   BOGOTA, Colombia (AP) _ A Colombian cargo plane trying to land
in dense fog crashed early Tuesday just outside the Medellin
airport, killing all five people on board.
	   The Russian-built Antonov carrying morning newspapers went down
just after midnight, 30 minutes after leaving Bogota for Jose Maria
Cordova airport in Colombia's second largest city.
	   Airport officials said the plane struck ground about a half-mile
(a kilometer) from the runway and broke into pieces, throwing the
three-man crew and two passengers over a wide area.
	   Authorities have not determined the cause of the crash, but poor
visibility was suspected.
