<SLUG> BC-Sweden-Store Fire,0140 </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Fire hits Swedish department store during Christmas rush
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   STOCKHOLM, Sweden (AP) _ Fire broke out in a Stockholm
department store crowded with Christmas shoppers Tuesday after
someone poured gasoline on a lower floor. At least two people were
injured.
	   Police said they arrested one person in connection with the
fire, the Swedish news agency TT reported.
	   The store faces Hoetorget square, directly across from
Stockholm's main concert hall. Firefighters closed the square,
which has about 20 covered stalls for vendors of produce, leather
and woolen goods.
	   One of the injured was taken to a hospital and treated for smoke
inhalation. Details on the injury to the other person were not
immediately known.
	   The fire was declared extinguished about 45 minutes after the
alarm sounded.
