<SLUG> BC-Georgia-Abkhazia </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Georgia accuses Russian peacekeepers of firing at its troops
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   TBILISI, Georgia (AP) _ The Georgian government on Tuesday
accused Russian peacekeepers of triggering a gun battle in the
breakaway province of Abkhazia that led to the death of a Georgian
soldier.
	   The shooting took place late Monday, when Russian peacekeepers
in Abkhazia shelled a Georgian military outpost without
provocation, the Georgian side claimed.
	   The Abkhazian separatists used the shelling as a cover to bypass
the Georgian soldiers and attack them from the rear, the Georgians
said.
	   An 19-year-old Georgian soldier was badly wounded and died in a
hospital early Tuesday, the Georgian Interior Ministry said in a
statement.
	   The Georgians urged the Russian military to investigate the
shooting and punish those responsible.
	   The spokesman for the Russian peacekeepers, Col. Valery
Pokushayev, rejected the Georgian version of events, saying the
Russian ``peacekeepers only open fire when they come under
shelling.''
	   Russian peacekeepers have been deployed in Abkhazia since 1994,
following a truce that ended a 1992-93 war in which Abkhazian
separatists drove out Georgian government troops.
	   The region has remained restive, plagued by frequent clashes.
The Georgian officials have often accused the Russian peacekeepers
of backing the separatists _ a charge they deny.
	   (md/vi/gm) 	   
