<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-Bulgaria-Blasts </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Two bingo halls blasted
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   SOFIA, Bulgaria (AP)_ Bomb explosions rocked two bingo halls in
Bulgaria's second biggest city Tuesday, the state news agency BTA
reported. Nobody was injured.
	   One of the blasts broke window panes and the other damaged a
car. Both occurred in Plovdiv, 160 kilometers (100 miles) southeast
of Sofia.
	   Bombings and shoot-outs have become a commonplace in Bulgaria in
the nearly 10 years since the end of communist rule in 1989. Crime
has surged fivefold since then.
	   A former athlete, believed to be a local underworld boss, was
shot to death last Sunday near Sofia.
	   In separate incidents over the past two weeks, a businessman in
central Bulgaria was killed by a car bomb and a police chief in
western Bulgaria had his home bombed.
	   (vz/gj)
</TEXT>
