<TEXT>
	   GENEVA (AP) _ The former honorary consul of Paraguay in Geneva,
Gustavo Gramont Beres, appeared before a magistrate in the city
Tuesday on charges of a dlrs 100 million fraud.
	   Beres, who had been charged for other offenses in Paraguay, was
extradited to Switzerland on the request of Geneva authorities,
said investigating magistrate Leonardo Malfanti.
	   Beres, an Argentine national, was the Paraguayan honorary consul
