<HEADLINE>
Five killed in bar by unknown assailant
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   ZAGREB, Croatia (AP) _ Five men were killed in the eastern city
of Pozega when a man entered a bar and sprayed them with
submachine-gun fire, officials said Tuesday.
	   An unidentified suspect was arrested a few hours after the
shooting occurred late Monday, Pozega district judge Nenad Vlasic
said in a statement. Neither the judge nor the police gave any
details of the shooting in the town situated 174 kilometers (109
miles) from Zagreb.
