r i &Cx13;  &Cx11;  BC-Netherlands-ChildPorn     12-22 0239
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-Netherlands-Child Porn </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Former civil servant convicted in child porn scandal
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   THE HAGUE, Netherlands (AP) _ A former government employee was
convicted Tuesday of downloading pedophilia and other pornography
from the Internet and storing it on a Justice Ministry computer.
	   The 39-year-old man, whose name was not released in line with
Dutch privacy laws, was sentenced to four months' imprisonment
commuted to 172 hours of unpaid public work.
	   Prosecutors had asked a three-judge panel at Hague District
Court for a six-month sentence for the former civil servant, who
was the Justice Ministry's computer systems manager at the time of
the offense.
	   The man was fired last summer when it was found that he had
downloaded thousands of pornographic images, including some of
children being abused, and stored them on computers at his office
and home.
	   He claimed in court that he did not know the pornography he
downloaded included images of children.
	   News of his dismissal and arrest came to light in August as the
nation struggled to come to terms with a scandal unleashed by the
discovery of a huge stash of child pornography which a Dutch-based
ring sold via the Internet to pedophiles all over the world. The
civil servant was not connected to that ring.
	   Possession of child pornography carries a maximum sentence of
six years' imprisonment in the Netherlands.
	   (mc/bk)
</TEXT>
