<SLUG> BC-Sports-Soccer-Manchester United-Moyes </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Preston owner talks down manager's move to Old Trafford
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   PRESTON, England (AP) _ Preston owner Bryan Gray on Tuesday
dispelled rumors that Manchester United was about to sign its
successful manager David Moyes as Alex Ferguson's No. 2.
	   ``It's flattering for David, but there's nothing happening,''
said the chairman of the division two club, which faces defending
titlist Arsenal in the third round of the FA Cup Jan. 4. ``There
has been no contact, and I'm not expecting any from them to be
honest.
	   ``I would not agree to it but I think we're talking about things
which are hypothetical.''
	   Reports linked United with 35-year-old Moyes who has lifted the
once-great club to fourth in the division two standings and on
course for a return to division one for the first time since 1981.
And he's done it without being able to buy any big names.
	   United has not won in five games since Brian Kidd, who had been
Ferguson's No. 2 for seven years, moved on to become manager of
Blackburn. Last Saturday the Reds lost 3-2 at home to Middlesbrough
and squandered a chance to go top of the Premier League.
	   (rjm) 	   
