<HEADLINE>
Anti-Euro demonstrators target central bank's party
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   UTRECHT, Netherlands (AP) _ A group of squatters protesting the
introduction of the single European currency attacked a concert
hall where the staff of the Dutch central bank were holding a
Christmas party, pelting the building with eggs and smashing
windows.
	   About 50 squatters attacked the Vredenburg hall in Utrecht, 50
kilometers (31 miles) east of Amsterdam, where 350 staff members
from the Netherlands Bank were partying Monday night.
	   Police called to break up the protest arrested five
demonstrators, Dutch television news reported Tuesday.
	   The single European currency, the euro, will debut on paper on
Jan. 1. Euro coins and notes come into circulation in the 11
participating nations by June 30, 2002.
