<SLUG> BC-Slovakia-Elections </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Members of government coalition parties do well in municipal
</HEADLINE>
elections

<TEXT>
	   BRATISLAVA, Slovakia (AP) _ More than 800 races in last
weekend's municipal elections were won my representatives of
political parties running the country in a coalition, official
results showed Tuesday.
	   Independent candidates also did well, with 816 of them among the
2,899 mayors elected. Representatives of the opposition Movement
for a Democratic Slovakia, headed by former Prime Minister Vladimir
Meciar won 602 races, and the nationalistic Slovak National Party
114.
	   Jozef Moravcik, a former prime minister and member of one of the
parties in the government coalition,was elected mayor of
Bratislava, the capital. Rudolf Schuster, the government's
candidate in presidential elections early next year, was reelected
mayor of Kosice, the second-largest city.
	   (al/gj)
