<HEADLINE>
SAfrica: Teachers, pupils with HIV must be allowed in school
</HEADLINE>
 &UR; Eds: ADDS time element for publishing of policy; picks up 4th graf
pvs, `South Africa's... &QL; 

<TEXT>
	   CAPE TOWN, South Africa (AP) _ Students and teachers infected
with the AIDS virus must be allowed to attend school and keep their
jobs, an education department spokesman said on Tuesday.
	   Though South Africa's constitution already defends such rights,
the government has recently drawn up policy protecting the 3
million South Africans with the HIV virus or AIDS from being
discriminated against in education.
	   ``This is a national policy to protect the rights of individuals
with AIDS,'' Bheki Khumalo said. The policy was set out in the
government gazette last Friday.
