<HEADLINE>
Politicians have to declare their assets
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   SOFIA, Bulgaria (AP) _ Amidst growing public criticism of
widespread post-communist corruption, Parliament on Tuesday
approved draft legislation committing senior government officials
to declare incomes and assets.
	   The drafts go to parliament for final approval within three
weeks. They apply to Bulgaria's president and vice president,
constitutional court judges, members of parliament, supreme court
judges, government minister, district governors and their deputies
and others.
	   Declarations will also be filed by family members on real
estate, bank deposits of 2 million leva (dlrs 1,200) and over,
securities, cars and second or third incomes.
