<SLUG> BC-Weather Summary,1222 </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Weather summary for Puerto Rico and the U.S. Virgin Islands
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   Weather summary for Puerto Rico and the U.S. Virgin Islands from
the National Weather Service.
	   An upper-level trough of low pressure has intensified across the
local area overnight and is producing unstable atmospheric
conditions in a narrow band extending from St. Croix northeastward
across the U.S. and British Virgin Islands.
	   Fresh northeast trade winds continue to usher patches and bands
of low level moisture underneath this trough to produce scattered
clusters of showers and isolated thunderstorms with a few bands of
showers continuing southwest and across portions of Puerto Rico.
	   This pattern will continue through the early part of the
afternoon before the most active weather begins to shift
southeastward and across the center of the Anegada Passage and into
the northern Leeward Islands.
	   Until that time, look for partly sunny skies across Puerto Rico
with occasional bands of showers moving quickly southwest through
the area.
	   Across the virgin islands, there will be occasional glimpses of
bright sunshine. Passing moderate to heavy showers will gradually
give way to a decrease in cloud cover and showers by late afternoon
or evening.
	   Surface high pressure continues to dominate most of the Atlantic
Ocean today and is maintaining fresh east-northeast trade winds
across the regional waters and rough seas offshore.
	   No significant changes in these marine conditions are expected
through tonight. A slight increase in winds and a decided increase
in the east-northeast trade wind swells are expected to move into
the local waters Wednesday, raising offshore seas to near 9 feet.
	   San Juan and the northern sections of Puerto Rico:
	   Today... Increasing morning cloudiness, becoming breezy.
Scattered to numerous showers. Slight chance of a thunderstorm.
Showers decreasing during the afternoon. High 80 to 85. Wind
northeast 15 to 20 mph. Chance of rain is 60 percent.
	   Tonight... Variably cloudy with a 40 percent chance of showers.
Low 70 to 75. Wind northeast to east at 5 to 10 mph.
	   Wednesday... Variably cloudy and breezy with a 50 percent chance
of showers. High 80 to 85. Wind northeast 15 to 20 mph.
	   Christmas forecast... Variable cloudiness with scattered
showers. High 80 to 85. Low 70 to 75.
	   Eastern sections of Puerto Rico:
	   Today... Mostly cloudy morning with scattered to numerous
showers. Slight chance of a thunderstorm, becoming partly sunny and
breezy by afternoon. High near 80 to 85. Chance of rain is 60
percent. Wind northeast 15 to 20 mph.
	   Tonight... Variably cloudy with a 40 percent chance of showers.
Low 70 to 75. Wind northeast 10 to 15 mph.
	   Wednesday... Variably cloudy and breezy with a 50 percent chance
of showers. High 80 to 85. Wind northeast 15 to 20 mph.
	   Christmas forecast... Variable cloudiness with scattered
showers. High 80 to 85. Low 70 to 75.
	   Ponce and the southern sections of Puerto Rico:
	   Today... Partly sunny and becoming breezy. A 30 percent chance
of showers. Slight chance of a thunderstorm. High 85 to 90. Wind
northeast 15 to 20 mph, except southeast along the coast.
	   Tonight... Variably cloudy with a 30 percent chance of showers.
Low 65 to 70. Wind northeast 5 to 10 mph.
	   Wednesday... Variably cloudy and breezy with a 50 percent chance
of showers. High 80 to 85. Wind northeast 15 to 20 mph, except
southeast along the coast.
	   Christmas forecast... Variable cloudiness with scattered
showers. High 85 to 90. Low 65 to 75.
	   Mayaguez and the western sections of Puerto Rico:
	   Today... Variable cloudiness and continued breezes. A 40 percent
chance of showers. High 80 to 85. Wind northeast 10 to 15 mph,
except 15 to 20 mph with higher gusts on the northwest coast.
	   Tonight... Variably cloudy with a 30 percent chance of showers.
Low 65 to 70. Wind northeast 5 to 10 mph, except 10 to 15 mph on
the northwest coast.
	   Wednesday... Variably cloudy and breezy with a 50 percent chance
of showers. High 80 to 85. Wind northeast 10 to 15 mph, except 15
to 20 mph with higher gusts on the northwest coast.
	   Christmas forecast... Variable cloudiness with scattered
showers. High 80 to 85. Low 70 to 75.
	   Interior sections of Puerto Rico:
	   Today... Variable cloudiness and breezy with a 50 percent chance
of showers. Slight chance of a thunderstorm. High 70 to 75
mountains to 75 to 80 low elevations. Wind northeast 15 to 25 mph.
	   Tonight... Variably cloudy with a 40 percent chance of showers.
Low 60 to 65. Wind northeast 15 to 20 mph.
	   Wednesday... Variably cloudy and breezy with a 50 percent chance
of showers. High 70 to 75 mountains to 75 to 80 low elevations.
Wind northeast 15 to 25 mph.
	   Christmas forecast... Variable cloudiness with scattered
showers. High 70 to 80. Low 60 to 70.
	   St. Thomas, St. John and the Adjacent Islands-St. Croix:
	   Today... Mostly cloudy morning with scattered showers. Slight
chance of a thunderstorm. Becoming partly sunny and breezy
afternoon. High near 85. Wind northeast 15 to 20 mph. Chance of
rain 50 percent.
	   Tonight... Variably cloudy with a 40 percent chance of showers.
Low 70 to 75. Wind northeast 10 to 15 mph
	   Wednesday... Variably cloudy and breezy with a 50 percent chance
of showers. High 80 to 85. Wind northeast 15 to 20 mph
	   Christmas forecast... Variable cloudiness with scattered
showers. High near 85. Low 70 to 75.
	   Atlantic waters north and northeast of Puerto Rico and the U.S.
Virgin Islands:
	   Small craft advisory in effect.
	   This afternoon... Wind northeast 15 to 20 kt. Seas 6 to 8 ft in
northeast swells. Scattered showers, more numerous in the northeast
waters. Isolated thunderstorms.
	   Tonight... Wind northeast to east 15 to 20 kt. Seas 5 to 7 ft in
northeast swells. Scattered showers, more numerous in the northeast
waters. Isolated thunderstorms.
	   Wednesday... Wind northeast 15 to 25 kt. Seas building 7 to 9 ft
in northeast swells. Scattered showers.
	   Caribbean waters south and southeast of Puerto Rico and the U.S.
Virgin Islands:
	   Small craft, exercise caution.
	   This afternoon... Wind northeast to east at 15 to 20 kt. Seas 5
to 7 ft. Scattered showers. Isolated thunderstorms.
	   Tonight... Wind northeast to east 15 to 20 kt. Seas 5 to 7 ft.
Scattered to numerous showers. Isolated thunderstorms.
	   Wednesday... Wind northeast 15 to 20 kt. Seas building 6 to 8
ft. Scattered showers.
	   Near shore waters of western Puerto Rico:
	   Small craft, exercise caution in outer waters.
	   This afternoon... Wind northeast to east at 10 to 20 kt. Seas 2
to 4 ft. Scattered showers.
	   Tonight... Wind northeast to east at 10 to 15 kt. Seas 2 to 4
ft. Scattered showers.
	   Wednesday... Wind northeast to east 10 to 20 kt. Seas 2 to 4 ft.
Widely scattered showers.
	   Outlook for Puerto Rico and the U.S. Virgin Islands waters:
	   Wednesday night through Saturday... Wind northeast to east at 20
kt or greater. Seas increasing 7 to 9 ft in Atlantic and Caribbean
waters.
</TEXT>
