<HEADLINE>
Judge orders trial for man in Bahamas tourist slaying
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   NASSAU, Bahamas (AP) _ A judge has ordered a 19-year-old to
stand trial for the murders of two tourists on the Bahamian resort
area of Paradise Island.
	   Magistrate Cheryl Albury handed down the decision Monday
following two weeks of preliminary hearings into the case. She did
not set a date for the trial.
	   Prosecutors claim Terrell McIntosh killed Lori Fogleman, a
schoolteacher from Richmond, Virginia, in July and left her body
near popular Cabbage Beach. She was last seen alive on July 20.
	   McIntosh is also charged him with raping and killing Joanne
Clarke of Oxfordshire, England, on Aug. 21.
	   Prosecutors are seeking the death penalty.
	   McIntosh is also charged with stealing Clarke's camera and dlrs
450 in travelers' checks; and with stealing two handbags and dlrs
310 in cash from Fogleman.
	   McIntosh was arrested Aug. 22 but released because of a lack of
evidence. Police arrested him again in September, saying forensic
tests led to the new charges.
</TEXT>
