<SLUG> BC-Russia-US-Iraq </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Russia's ambassador to Washington returning after recall
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   MOSCOW (AP) _ Russia's ambassador to the United States, recalled
to protest the bombing of Iraq, will return to Washington on
Wednesday, an official said.
	   Foreign Ministry spokesman Vladimir Rakhmanin said Tuesday that
Russia didn't want to ``complicate'' its relations with the United
States ``now that the United States has stopped its action, as
Russia insisted,'' the Interfax news agency reported.
	   Ambassador Yuly Vorontsov was recalled last week, as was
Russia's ambassador to Britain.
	   President Boris Yeltsin and Russian leaders across the political
spectrum denounced the U.S. and British attacks on Iraq and
demanded an immediate halt to the campaign. Several top officials
warned that the attacks would hurt Russian-US relations.
	   (ad/adc)
