<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-Netherlands-Ax Attack,0150 </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Police hunt father who attacked son with ax
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   AMSTERDAM, Netherlands (AP) _ Police in the Dutch capital were
involved in a manhunt Tuesday for a father who hacked at his
7-year-old son's head with an ax, leaving the child fighting for
his life.
	   The boy was taken to a hospital with serious injuries to his
head and neck following Monday's attack. His condition was
described as critical but stable late Tuesday.
	   His father, a 34-year-old man, is in the middle of acrimonious
divorce proceedings with the child's mother, Amsterdam police said.
	   The man was visiting his son at a family friend's house. When he
saw the child, he pulled a meat cleaver and ax out from under his
clothing and attacked him.
	   The youngster managed to escape but his father chased him down a
street, caught him and hit him in the head with the ax before
fleeing.
</TEXT>
