<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-Albania </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Students end hunger strike
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   TIRANA, Albania (AP) _ Student protesters in Albania ended a
hunger strike Tuesday after the government agreed to meet some of
their demands for better conditions.
	   About 40 students on Tuesday ended their 12-day long hunger
strike, when the state said it would invest more money into
realizing better water and energy conditions in the dormitories. It
also said scholarships would go up 10-20 percent from the current
dlrs 30 to 35.
	   ``It's really a good thing reaching such conclusion, even if it
is late'' said Besnik Jaku, a 22-year-old striker.
	   Albanian Minister of Education Et'hem Ruka asked that the
students be patient with the meeting of their requests, ``since we
are talking about 10,000 students who are living in dorms.''
	   The hunger strike began on Dec. 10 in a disco in the Tirana
University dormitory complex. Students from Shkodra University, in
northern Albania, later joined in the protest.
	   One week later, police entered the dormitory and broke up the
strike, because the authorities said one of the students was
suffering from hepatitis C.
	   The students resumed the strike the same day, supported by
Democratic leader Sali Berisha.
	   On Monday, Berisha met with Albanian Prime Minister Pandeli
Majko to discuss the strike.
	   (ac/me) 	   
</TEXT>
