<SLUG> BC-Sports-Soccer-Brazil-Zagallo,0143 </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Zagallo reportedly to coach Portuguesa
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   RIO DE JANEIRO, Brazil (AP) _ Months after losing the World Cup
final and his job, former Brazilian national team coach Mario
Zagallo has agreed to coach Portuguesa, the Globo TV network
reported Tuesday.
	   Portuguesa, for years a second-level club in Sao Paulo, has
emerged as a national contender in recent years. It reached the
finals of the Brazilian championship in 1996 and the semifinals
this year.
	   Zagallo, 67, won the World Cup as a player in 1958 and 1962, as
coach in 1970 and as team coordinator in 1994. His only loss came
this year, when Brazil lost the final 3-0 to France.
	   Zagallo also has coached clubs in Brazil and the Middle East. He
would replace Candinho, who quit after Portuguesa was eliminated by
Cruzeiro in the semifinals.
</TEXT>
