<DOC>
<DOCNO> APW19981222.0913 </DOCNO>
<DOCTYPE> NEWS STORY </DOCTYPE>
<DATE_TIME> 12/22/1998 14:32:00 </DATE_TIME>
<HEADER>
w1951 &Cx1f; wstm-
r f &Cx13;  &Cx11;  BC-Germany-Euro 2ndLd-Writethru   12-22 0628
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-Germany-Euro, 2nd Ld-Writethru </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
ECB announces two further interest rates for post-Jan. 1 euro zone
</HEADLINE>
 &UR; Eds: CLARIFIES overline &QL; 
 &UR; By DIDI KIRSTEN TATLOW &QC; 
 &UR; Associated Press Writer &QC; 

<TEXT>
	   FRANKFURT, Germany (AP) _ In a novel approach reflecting the
uncertainties of the Jan. 1 launch of Europe's new currency, the
