<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-Sports-Soccer-Baggio-Knife </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
Suspect arrested in UEFA Cup knife-throwing incident
</HEADLINE>

<TEXT>
	   WARSAW, Poland (AP) _ Police on Tuesday arrested a 19-year-old
man who allegedly threw a knife that struck Italian soccer player
Dino Baggio, injuring him during a UEFA Cup match in Krakow in
October.
	   The PAP state news agency reported the man, identified as Pawel
Michalski, was arrested in Krakow, according to Malgorzata
Wilkosz-Sliwa, a spokeswoman for the local prosecutor's office.
	   If convicted of throwing the knife that injured Baggio, the
suspect could receive a sentence of up to 10 years in prison.
	   Baggio was hit by a knife thrown from the stands in the 80th
minute of the second-round, first-leg match between AC Parma and
Wisla Krakow on Oct. 20. He needed five stitches to close a head
wound.
	   The teams tied 1-1, and AC Parma won the second game 2-1 at home
to advance 3-2 on aggregate.
	   UEFA banned Wisla Krakow from European competition for one year,
meaning the club will be disqualified from the first European
competition it qualifies to compete in over the next five years.
	   (bp-tsc)
</TEXT>
