<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-AP-Sports Digest,0799 </SLUG>


<TEXT>
	   WORLD SPORTS AT 0000 GMT
 &UR; SOCCER:
	   ZURICH, Switzerland _ European champion Germany will replace
World Cup winner France in next year's Confederations' Cup in
Mexico.
	   Slug Sports-Soccer-Confederations Cup. Has moved.
	   BIRMINGHAM, England _ Mark Bosnich may have played his last game
for Aston Villa. After six seasons as the club's No. 1 goalkeeper,
the 26-year-old Australian, who has turned down several offers of a
new contract, is out of the team because of a shoulder injury and
manager John Gregory is looking for a replacement.
	   Slug Sports-Soccer-Villa-Bosnich. Has moved.
	   ALSO:
	   _ BRUSSELS, Belgium _ Sports-Soccer-Bosman. Has moved. By Anna
Sathiah
	   _ PARIS _ Sports-Soccer-Paris Saint-German. Has moved.
	   _ PRESTON, England _ Sports-Soccer-Manchested United-Moyes. Has
moved.
	   _ SOUTHAMPTON, England _ Sports-Soccer-Saints-Kachloul. Has
moved.
 &UR; OLYMPICS:
	   NEW YORK _ Hoping to calm jittery sponsors and avoid future
mistakes, Northern Ireland peace negotiator and former U.S. Senate
leader George Mitchell is selected to head a U.S. Olympic Committee
investigation of bribery allegations in Salt Lake's successful bid
for the 2002 Winter Games.
	   Slug Sports-Olympics-IOC-Bribes. Has moved.
	   By Larry Siddons.
	   ALSO:
	   _ WARSAW, Poland _ Sports-Olympics-Poland. Has moved.
 &UR; GOLF:
	   LONDON _ Barely three years ago before Tiger Woods made his
phenomenal impact on the game, Nick Faldo was the bookmakers
favorite to win any of the Majors. After the worst slump of his
spectacular career, he's now quoted at 40-1 to win the Masters, the
British Open or the PGA and 50-1 for the US Open.
	   Slug Sports-Golf-Faldo-Odds. Has moved.
	   ORLANDO, Florida _ Golf is as global as it ever has been, and
getting bigger. Big enough even for the Ryder Cup or Presidents Cup
to make room for other international events.
	   Slug Sports-Golf-Ryder Cup. Has moved.
	   By Doug Ferguson.
	   Also:
	   _ ORLANDO, Florida _ Sports-Golf Notes. By Doug Ferguson. Has
moved.
 &UR; TENNIS:
	   ZAGREB, Croatia _ The father of Goran Ivanisevic and the head of
the Croatian tennis federation have been found guilty of slandering
each other, Croatian media reports Tuesday.
	   Slug Sports-Tennis-Croatia-Ivanisevic. Has moved.
	   SYDNEY, Australia _ Reigning Australian Open tennis title-holder
Petr Korda fails a drug test at the 1998 Wimbledon Championships,
the International Tennis Federation says Wednesday.
	   Slug Sports-Tennis-Drugs-Korda. Has moved.
 &UR; AUTO RACING:
	   VANCOUVER, British Columbia _ It took almost three months to
satisfy safety and hospitality concerns, but organizers have
convinced Championship Auto Racing Teams to return in September for
the Vancouver Molson Indy.
	   Slug Sports-Auto Racing-Vancouver-Indy. Has moved.
 &UR; HORSE RACING:
	   HONG KONG _ Twice a week, 45 weeks a year, a fifth of the people
in Hong Kong get caught up in the territory's sporting obsession _
betting on horse races. Asia's economic downturn, however, has Hong
Kong gamblers putting less money down on the ponies.
	   Slug Sports-Horse Racing-Hong Kong-Racing Slowdown. Expected by
0200 GMT.
	   By Tara Suilen Duffy.
 &UR; AMERICAN FOOTBALL:
	   DENVER _ For 13 weeks, the Denver Broncos were unbeatable.
Suddenly, with the playoffs looming, they've lost two straight
games.
	   Slug Sports-Football-Staggering Broncos. Has moved.
