<TEXT>
	   WORLD AT 0000 GMT
	    &UR; NEW:
	   _GERMANY-NUCLEAR. Schroeder raps minister over nuclear shutdown.
	   _BETHLEHEM-CHRISTMAS BLUES. Mideast turmoil hurting Christmas
tourism.
	   _US-ASTEROID MISSION. Asteroid orbit mission postponed.
	    &UR; MAIN SPOT NEWS:
	   WASHINGTON _ Battling to save the U.N. weapons inspection
system, the U.S. government stands firm on the authority of Richard
Butler and his commission to decide how to operate in Iraq.
US-IRAQ. Lead has moved. By Barry Schweid.
	   ALSO MOVED:
	   _UN-IRAQ. Security Council starts discussing steps to map new
Iraq policy. AP Photos NYR106-107, NYR110-111.
	   _IRAQ. Baghdad claims new missile attack on Tuesday.
	   WASHINGTON _ After miscalculating in the House, President Bill
Clinton's defenders are assembling a Senate plan that for now will
put lawyerly defenses on the back bench in favor of an aggressive
lobbying effort for censure. US-CLINTON-IMPEACHMENT. Recap expected
by 0200 GMT. By John Solomon. AP Photos AWH401.
	   With: US-IMPEACHMENT-POLL.
	   JERUSALEM _ Ehud Barak faces an uphill battle: a contest for the
prime minister's job with Benjamin Netanyahu, a media-savvy
politician with a talent for selling himself. So the opposition
leader is fighting back with some high-priced American spin
doctors. TAKING ON BIBI. Has moved. By Nicolas B. Tatro. AP Photo
JRL103-104.
	   ALSO MOVED:
	   _ISRAEL-POLITICS. Netanyahu to face numerous challengers. AP
Photos JRL101-102, TLV101-102.
	   _US-ISRAEL. Despite political turmoil, U.S. says Israel should
withdraw from West Bank.
	   _LEBANON-ISRAEL. Israeli warplanes kill a woman and her six
children.
	   _PALESTINIAN-ISRAEL. Palestinians plan to release Hamas leader
this week.
	   WASHINGTON _ The Federal Reserve decides to leave interest rates
unchanged, and may hold off until well into next year before
cutting rates again. US-ECONOMY-INTEREST RATES. Recap expected by
0200 GMT. By Dave Skidmore.
	   ALSO: GERMANY-EURO. In a bid for stable currency launch, Europe
sets interest rates in narrow range. Recap expected by 0200 GMT.
